## CSS Selectors

**CSS selectors** are used to target specific elements in an HTML document and apply styles to them. They act like filters, identifying elements based on various criteria.

**Types of Selectors:**

1.  **Element Selectors:** Target elements based on their tag name.
      - Example: `p` (targets all paragraph elements)
2.  **Class Selectors:** Target elements based on their class attribute.
      - Example: `.my-class` (targets elements with the class "my-class")
3.  **ID Selectors:** Target elements based on their unique ID attribute.
      - Example: `#my-id` (targets the element with the ID "my-id")
4.  **Attribute Selectors:** Target elements based on their attributes.
      - Example: `[href]` (targets elements with the "href" attribute)
5.  **Pseudo-class Selectors:** Target elements based on their state or condition.
      - Example: `:hover` (targets elements when hovered over)

**Example HTML Document:**

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>CSS Selectors</title>
    <style>
        /* Element Selector */
        p {
            color: blue;
        }

        /* Class Selector */
        .highlight {
            background-color: yellow;
        }

        /* ID Selector */
        #my-heading {
            font-size: 24px;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        /* Attribute Selector */
        a[href="https://example.com"] {
            color: green;
        }

        /* Pseudo-class Selector */
        button:hover {
            background-color: lightgray;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1 id="my-heading">Heading</h1>
    <p>This is a paragraph.</p>
    <p class="highlight">Highlighted paragraph.</p>
    <a href="https://example.com">Link to Example</a>
    <button>Hover me</button>
</body>
</html>
```

**Explanation:**

- The `p` selector styles all paragraph elements with blue text.
- The `.highlight` selector styles elements with the class "highlight" with a yellow background.
- The `#my-heading` selector styles the element with the ID "my-heading" with a larger font size and bold weight.
- The `a[href="https://example.com"]` selector styles links with the href attribute "[https://example.com](https://www.google.com/url?sa=E&source=gmail&q=https://example.com)" with green text.
- The `button:hover` selector styles buttons when hovered over with a light gray background.
